git_finalize dispatch caveat (witnessed iter27, 2026-06-07): writing the git_finalize request body via bash heredoc with literal \n sequences inside the JSON {message} STRING fails - git_finalize-7 returned {"error":"worktree dirty but no commit message provided"} because the heredoc-written \n broke the JSON parse (the watcher could not extract message). FIX: use the Write tool for structured JSON spool bodies (single-line message, real JSON escaping) - re-dispatching the SAME commit via Write tool (git_finalize-8) succeeded immediately (sha a628b453). This is the exact failure the SKILL.md boot prose warns about ("Use bash -c echo -n or Write tool instead when the body is structured JSON"). Reinforced rule: NEVER hand-author multi-line JSON spool bodies (git_finalize messages, prd-add titles with newlines) via bash heredoc; use the Write tool which guarantees clean UTF-8 no-BOM and correct escaping. The failure is silent-ish: git_finalize reports a misleading "no commit message" rather than a parse error, so the symptom looks like a missing field when the real cause is heredoc \n mangling.